idation_claims_enterprise_trust=false, human_final_approval_required_for_runtime_opening=true) + M05 binding rows that never evaluate/write permission or audit + M06 fixture rows with no real data + Hermes emits_runtime_receipt=false + Claude read_only/promotes_claude_to_final_approval=false + handoff to_pack_id, and contract promotion of CP00-797 with cp788-cp797 projections; index.js export* surfaces all CP797 symbols and the service-layer contract builder agrees with the committed contract (latest_pack/latest_projection=cp797, validation.valid=true), which the updated scripts/validate-rp26-enterprise-saas-hardening-contract.mjs re-checks. Authority boundaries hold: Claude is a read-only independent reviewer (review-request read_only=true, tools Read,Grep,Glob), not final approver, and Hermes is used only as a descriptor-only/control-plane evidence+review-receipt pattern, not embedded product runtime - matching the stated authority boundary. Review-hardening preconditions are satisfied: auth preflight passed (exit 0, 1226-byte valid JSON, non-empty), model claude-opus-4-8 / effort max / read_only, tools Read,Grep,Glob with forbidden_tools_present=false, prompt 2508 bytes within the 25600 limit, and no invalid review attempts. The pack does not over-claim: manifest production_ready=false, runtime_ready=false, implementation_layer=descriptor, descriptor_only=true, pack_level_claude_review.status=pending. Two non-blocking P3 observations are recorded: the closeout finalization artifacts (command-evidence.json, adjudication.md, construction-inspection.json, and this receipt's claude-review-result.json) are not present at review time, so the 10 validation-command exit codes could not be independently re-run by this read-only review - that verification is deferred to and deterministically enforced by npm run closeout-pack:validate, which requires all required commands at exit 0, a PASS/PASS_WITH_FINDINGS verdict with 0 P0/P1/P2, adjudication "Production ready after adjudication: yes", and inspection verdict PASS before the manifest may flip to production_ready; and a cosmetic changed-file-scope.json double-classification carryover. No P0/P1/P2 findings.","findings":[{"id":"CP797-001","severity":"P3","title":"Closeout finalization artifacts pending this review receipt; validation-command results not independently re-runnable","file":"docs/closeout-packs/cp00-797/manifest.json","line":527,"details":"At review time docs/closeout-packs/cp00-797/ contains only manifest.json; command-evidence.json, adjudication.md, and construction-inspection.json (and this receipt's claude-review-result.json) are absent. These are produced during closeout finalization after the review receipt - confirmed by validate-closeout-pack.mjs, where validateCommandEvidence/validateClaudeReview/validateInspection/validateAdjudication short-circuit while manifest.status is in_progress and only fully enforce once status flips to production_ready, and where command-evidence's required command set includes 'npm run closeout-pack:validate' (which itself reads claude-review-result.json/construction-inspection.json), so command-evidence cannot precede the review. Because this reviewer is read-only with no Bash, the 10 expected validation commands (closeout-pack-plan/closeout-pack/test/validate/spec:requirements/weighted/fullplan/goal:closeout/rp00:control-plane + git diff --check) could not be independently executed; their results are not yet captured in-repo. This is expected workflow ordering, not a defect: the manifest is not yet claiming production_ready, and the closeout-pack:validate gate deterministically blocks the production_ready flip unless every required command shows exit_code 0, the Claude verdict is PASS/PASS_WITH_FINDINGS with 0 P0/P1/P2, adjudication states 'Production ready after adjudication: yes', and inspection verdict is PASS.","recommendation":"No action required before this receipt. During finalization, ensure command-evidence.json records all r